text_Basalt: Solid, dark color (brown, black, grey), dull but relatively smooth surface with jagged edges.
text_Gabbro: Speckled appearance, almost blotchy. Different types of edges. Often grey, brown black with light color throughout.

text_Diorite: Heavy contrast between light rock and dark speckles. white or light base really shows through splotches. Somewhat smooth surface, more rounded edges but not all
text_Peridotite: Minimal contrast between speckles/coloring. grey tones with white or yellow/green hues. speckling is minimal and more just discoloration. More sharp edges, rougher surface.

text_Diorite: White and dark contrast is heavy. speckling is more spreadout but consistent, can see the light base under the dark speckles
text_Pegmatite: Irregular and 'different material' chunks throughout base rock. Often light colored base with odd, or colorful or jagged chunks throughout.
